	<p>Hi, I'm Tip ten Brink / Hey, ik ben Tip ten Brink (Dutch below). I was born April 5th, 2000 in the city of Amsterdam, in my home country of the Netherlands. Today, I am a student at the Delft University of Technology (TU Delft), where I graduated with a double BSc degree in Applied Mathematics and Applied Physics. Currently, I am pursuing my MSc in Computer Science. I also live in Delft.</p>

	<p>In 2003, I moved to Chicago, in the United States. I returned to the Netherlands in 2006, moving to Baarn. I only left Baarn when I started studying in 2018.</p>

	<p>I did not study well during the pandemic. To remain busy, I worked part-time at Picnic, an online supermarket, cycling 18 km to their Rotterdam warehouse. Since 2018 I have provided exam training (for final-year high school students) at Stichting Studiebegeleiding Leiden for multiple weekends per year. Since 2023 I've been involved with building software for SimplyMeals, an innovative startup that delivers warm, healthy group meals.</p>

	<p>I like to spend my free time on many things. As can be gathered from the topics of this website, I am very interested in technology, politics, math, space, and any kind of other science. I also enjoy programming, reading and writing. The latter mostly involves worldbuilding, details of which I like to share occasionally. I love watching movies and I like my TV shows too, maybe I'll share some tips one day. I also play sports, I am active at the Delft track and field student association, D.S.A.V. Dodeka, where I mostly do long-distance running. Within Dodeka I'm also active for the website committee, the .ComCom.</p>

